A controller may use electronic means for the purpose of disseminating marketing messages only if the data subject has consented to receiving such messages (referred to as “solicited messages”).&nbsp;
A data subject has the ability to opt-out of receiving solicited messages free of charge. A controller must provide information to the data subject on how to opt-out of the solicited messages, both at the time of collecting contact information and each time a message is sent to the data subject.&nbsp;Last modified 21 Dec 2021
				
			